Questionnaire 3D body posturesInizio blocco: Consent formQID1 Welcome to the study on subjective judgement of body poses.     This questionnaire consists of multiple blocks, where one random picture of a 3D human model performing an action will be shown. It will be followed by a set of 10 questions, and in total, the whole experiment is expected to take 1h30minutes to complete. More details regarding the procedure will be further explained in the next sections.     Upon its completion you will receive a  reward that can be redeemed via 3 options(1.5 SONA credits, VVV voucher and Reimbursement equivalent to 15 euros ). At the end of the experiment, you will be guided on how to do it.  Your participation in the study is voluntary and you can withdraw your participation at anytime. The data collected here will only be used for research purposes and will not be publicly disclosed.  In case you still have any questions, please feel free to contact: g.marrazzo@maastrichtuniversity.nl  Do you consent to this terms? o Yes, I consent to the terms above  (1) o No, I do not consent  (2) Interruzione di pagina
Fine blocco: Consent formInizio blocco: DemographicsQID9 What is your Nationality?    ________________________________________________________________QID111 Are you left- or right-handed? o Right  (1) o Left  (2) QID3 What is your date of birth? (dd/mm/yyyy)    ________________________________________________________________QID4 What Gender do you identify yourself with?o Male  (1) o Female  (2) o Non-binary / third gender  (3) o Prefer not to say  (4) QID5 What Ethinicity do you identify yourself with?o White  (1) o Black  (2) o Asian  (3) o Other  (4) ________________________________________________QID10 Do you possess any kind of visual Impairments or  neurological conditions ? (If yes, please state which)    ________________________________________________________________QID11 What is your e-mail address?    ________________________________________________________________Interruzione di pagina
Fine blocco: DemographicsInizio blocco: INTROQID32 In the next page the study will start. As soon as you click on the forward button, a random picture depicting a body pose will be shown for 750ms and then hidden from the participant. It will be followed below by a set of 10 questions, which will ask about your  perception on the emotion and movement when looking at them. You will only be able to move to the next stimuli after 30 seconds, as well as answering all the questions.There will be 108 runs, once in every 12 runs, you will have the option to take a break of 1 minute before resuming with the questionnaire. Fine blocco: INTROInizio blocco: Stim_uparam_100_Viewpoint_1_scale_96QID112 Interruzione di pagina
QID113 Can you recognize a daily action in the posture?  (If yes, which one?)o Yes  (1) o No  (2) o Greeting a person  (3) o Grasping an object  (4) o Catching an object  (5) o Self-Defending  (6) o None of the above  (7) QID114 Do you feel this posture arousing or rather boring?Boring (1)  (2)  (3)  (4)Arousing (5)1 (1) o o o o o QID115 Do you feel this posture is positive or rather negative?Very Negative (1)  (2)  (3)  (4)Very Positive (5)1 (1) o o o o o QID116 Does the posture show any emotion? (if yes, which one?)o Yes  (9) o No  (8) o Sadness  (16) o Happiness  (17) o Fear  (18) o Disgust  (19) o Anger  (20) o Surprise  (21) QID117 How much body contraction is there in the body posture?Little contraction (1)  (2)  (3)  (4)A lot of contraction (5)1 (1) o o o o o QID118 How much overall body movement is implied in the posture? Little movement (1)  (2)  (3)  (4)A lot of movement (5)1 (1) o o o o o QID119 Is it possible for any of the body parts to be in this position or not?Possible (1)  (2)  (3)  (4)Impossible (5)  (1) o o o o o QID120 Is this a realistic body posture you can make yourself or is it an impossible one? Very unrealistic (1)  (2)  (3)  (4)Very realistic (5)1 (1) o o o o o QID121 Is this posture familiar to you? Very unfamiliar (1)  (2)  (3)  (4)Very familiar (5)1 (1) o o o o o QID122 TimingFirst Click  (1)Last Click  (2)Page Submit  (3)Click Count  (4)QID123 Which body part did you mostly look at?o Head  (1) o Hands  (2) o Arms  (3) o Legs  (4) o feet  (5) o Overall  (6) Interruzione di pagina
